Kim Jong Il Enjoys Art Performance Given by KPA Company Soldiers 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il enjoyed an art performance given by soldiers of companies under KPA Unit 682 and KPA Unit 3993 who participated in the 31st art festival of servicepersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were KPA General Hyon Chol Hae, KPA Lieut. General Jong Thae Gun and other commanding officers of the KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The repertoire of the performance included chorus "General Is with Soldiers", story-telling and song "Life at Company Is Good", accordion and song "Accordionist Has Come", solo "Longing for General", flute and duet "Ulnam, Donï¿½ft Cry", chorus "We'll Become Seventh Regiment Today" and other colorful numbers of diverse genres. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers enthusiastically sang of the invincible might of the heroic KPA and the servicepersons' happy service replete with optimism and joy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Watching the performance full of enthusiasm and sky-high spirit, Kim Jong Il expressed great satisfaction over the splendid performance flawless in its ideological content and artistry given by the soldiers of the companies. He highly appreciated their successful performance and extended thanks to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the soldiers have firmly prepared themselves politically and ideologically and in military technique and grown to be an army strong in idea and faith with high cultural entertainments, he said, adding that no force on earth can match such army ready to go through thick and thin for the sake of the party and the leader, the country and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the 31st art festival of servicepersons of the KPA is a striking demonstration of the validity and vitality of the WPK's literary and art policy on popularizing art and the praiseworthy culture of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The soldier culture created by the KPA is pervaded with the spirit of the times and militant optimism and rich emotion and it has become an example of socialist cultured practice in the era of Songun and a genuine model for all the officials and other working people to follow, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that it is an effective means for increasing the combat capability of the unit to energetically conduct the revolutionary art activities in the army, he set forth highly important tasks which would serve as guidelines for further developing the popular art activities.

Kim Yong Nam Receives Credentials from Myanmar Ambassador 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, received credentials from U Thein Lwin, Myanmar ambassador to the DPRK, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam had a talk with him after receiving it.

KCNA Blasts Bolton's Anti-DPRK Remarks 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- U.S. conservative hard-liners raised their heads again to malignantly slander the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Neo-con Bolton is typical of them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He talked trash that it is foolish to expect north Korea to keep its promise, history proves that it will never scrap its nuclear program of itself and it is a matter of time to realize that the U.S. has been fooled. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He even published a book titled "Surrender is not an option" in which he asserted that some mandarins of the U.S. administration are conducting absurd diplomatic negotiations with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bolton's remarks are not worth even a passing note as they are nothing but a spate of vituperation let loose by an ill-tempered guy ousted from the government. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is quite natural that one can hardly hear any proper remarks from Bolton as he is ill-famed for speaking ill of the countries standing for progress and peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What he uttered is no more than a shrill cry intended to tarnish the image of the DPRK well known to have kept its promise and faith. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What matters is that Bolton and other U.S. conservative hard-liners are working hard to scrap the agreement adopted at the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bolton has become busy visiting congressmen. This is evidenced by the facts that he urged lawmakers to oppose the above-said agreement and some congressmen from the Republican Party were of the view that they would not approve the expenses for the provision of heavy fuel oil to the DPRK requested by the administration and conservatives of the administration claimed that a stick should be applied to north Korea in case it fails to keep its promise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As universally known, the agreements adopted at the six-party talks stipulate the commitments to be fulfilled by the participants in the talks for the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Earnest talks are now under way between the DPRK and the U.S. in various fields including bilateral working-level talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. supply of heavy fuel oil to the DPRK is going on at the phase of implementation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, U.S. conservative hard-liners are keen to have the above-said agreement scrapped and deter the U.S. administration from implementing it. This is a clear indication that they do not wish to see the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula but only pursue a stand-off. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What the conservative hard-liners are doing will only invite the international community's censure as it is nothing but an anachronistic and base act of those who swim against the trend of the times toward detente over the nuclear issue of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No wonder, AP accused Bolton of working hard to scrap the agreement adopted at the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. conservative hard-liners would be well advised to behave themselves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent stand of the DPRK to denuclearize the Korean Peninsula. It remains unchanged in its sincere efforts to achieve this aim.

Message of Sympathy to Mexican President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Tuesday sent a message of sympathy to Felipe Calderon Hinojosa, President of Mexico, as regards the unprecedented torrential rain that caused great human and material losses in Mexico. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the message Kim hoped that the president and the government of Mexico would eradicate the aftermath of natural disaster as soon as possible and stabilize the life of the flood sufferers.

Staff Members of Chinese Embassy Help Korean Farmers 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- Ambassador Liu Xiaoming and staff members of the Chinese embassy here gave a helping hand to farmers of the DPRK-China Friendship Thaekam Co-op Farm in Sunan District, Pyongyang, on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They deepened the feeling of friendship, helping farmers in rice threshing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that he is pleased to work with farmers of the friendship farm, the ambassador hoped the farm would increase agricultural production in the future.

Day of Cuban National Culture Observed in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- An art exhibition opened under the sponsorship of the Cuban embassy here on the occasion of the day of the Cuban national culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The opening ceremony took place at the Pyongyang International Cultural Centre on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Vice-Chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Jon Yong Jin, officials concerned and working people in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were diplomatic envoys and officials of foreign embassies here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Ambassador Jose Manuel Galego Montano and staff members of the Cuban embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A speech was made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants looked round art works and handicrafts showing wisdom and talent of the Cuban people and cultural development of the Cuban nation.

DPRK to Make Positive Contribution to Worldwide Protection and Promotion of Human Rights 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- The DPRK will more firmly defend the advantageous socialist system of Korean style which legally and practically guarantees the people's enjoyment of human rights on the basis of the man-centered Juche idea and make a positive contribution to protecting and promoting human rights worldwide. A DPRK delegate said this when addressing the meeting of the Third Committee handling social, human rights and humanitarian issues of the 62nd UN General Assembly on October 31. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There go on the international arena at present unceasing acts of taking the lives of innocent people and violating the rights and basic freedom of people quite contrary to the trend of the times towards peace and stability, he noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to protect and promote human rights it is necessary to put an end to aggression against sovereign states and interference in their internal affairs and the application of the double standards and selectivity in dealing with human rights issues and eradicate national chauvinism prevalent in the developed countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the fact that xenophobia is frequently practiced and minorities are becoming targets of violence as a result of the emergence of neo-Nazism and ultra-right forces in different countries, he drew the attention of the above-said committee to the Japanese authorities' suppression of Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a wanton violation of the UN Charter which calls for respecting human rights and basic freedom of all people and major international laws on human rights as it is a heinous fascist act to physically remove the centre for activities of Koreans in Japan in a bid to suppress the activities of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan and Koreans in Japan, he noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has done all it could to protect and promote the rights of the people despite the ceaseless threat of aggression by the U.S. and other hostile forces and unprecedented economic blockade for nearly six decades since its founding. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people now fully enjoy the basic freedom and amply exercise their rights as the full-fledged master of the state and society.

Japanese Imperialists' Criminal Pillage of Forest Resources of Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- The Japanese imperialists had committed innumerable crimes unprecedented in history during their occupation of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their pillage of Korea's forest resources was nothing but part of their criminal acts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to data, they took more than 769,402,347 cubic meters of trees from Korea to Japan in the period from 1902 to July 1945. Among them were 219,282,347 cubic meters of timber, 522,820,000 cubic meters of firewood and 27,300,000 cubic meters of wood for charcoal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They plundered Korea of its rich forest resources in every vicious way to meet the economic and military demands for timber including paper -making, ship-building, construction and sleeper in their country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, they devastated the primeval forest of more than two million hectares in the areas along the Amnok and Tuman Rivers through four "Forest Management Stations" under direct control of the "Government-general of Korea," 26 deforestation companies and 100-odd tree-felling sites. Besides, they let "forest management agencies" under the 13 "provincial governments" and entrepreneurs and enterprises of Japan including the "Mitsui Local Products", "Sumitomo Big Business" and "Katakura Industry" to plunder a numerous forest resources in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Within three years after their occupation of Korea, the Japanese imperialists carried away some 48 million cubic meters of timber. They deforested over 3 million hectares of woodland by 1916 and over 118,000 hectares of woodland along large rivers including the Taedong, Han, Rakdong and Kum Rivers in 1919. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is part of the Japanese imperialists' plunder of forest resources. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan must clearly know the past crimes of the Japanese imperialists and apologize and compensate to the Korean people for them.

Pyongyang Indoor Stadium, Comprehensive Mass Sports Center
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- Pyongyang Indoor Stadium situated on the bank of the Pothong River flowing through Pyongyang is crowded with working people and school youth and children who are conducting sports activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, opened in April Juche 62 (1973), covers an area of 350,000 square meters and has a total floor space of about 70,000 square meters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is a ground of 4,600 square meters on the first floor of the stadium where 18 kinds of games can be held at a time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has training rooms for table-tennis, wrestling, judo, gymnastics, basketball, volleyball and boxing and folk playgrounds for Korean chess, paduk (go), etc. 
 It has well-furnished service facilities including the rooms of rest, shower, sauna and toilets for players. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are outside of the stadium three ponds covering more than 8,500 square meters, group sculptures depicting athletes and artistes and tennis, basketball and badminton courts and a roller skating ground. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The working people and school youth and children are enjoying their holidays, building up their bodies with various physical culture and sports activities there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Various sporting events for Mangyongdae Cup and Paektusan Cup, DPRK Championships and other games are held there every year.

Immortal Feats in Ushering in New Era of Juche-Oriented Revolutionary Drama
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- Thirty-five years have passed since Kim Jong Il marked a turning-point in the drama field. New revolutionary dramas have been created to enrich the Juche-oriented revolutionary drama art in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At that time, the world drama circle thought that it was inevitable for the drama with long history to fall into decay and ruin as movies were widely disseminated and TV found its way to houses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On November 7, Juche 61 (1972) Kim Jong Il authored the famous work "On Creating a New Revolutionary Drama that Meets the Juche Era". He in the work indicated the very way for creating new revolutionary dramas suitable to the emotion and aesthetic sense of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He heralded the drama revolution with the representation of the famous drama "A Mountain Shrine" created by President Kim Il Sung in the period of his early revolutionary activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In those days he gave scientific answers to the theoretic and practical issues arising in creation of revolutionary drama such as theme, composition and aspect of drama, introduction of music and song to drama, stereo of stage art, conversion of stage without letup and thus created a model of the Korean style revolutionary drama. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under his guidance brilliant successes were made in creating such famous works as "Blood at an International Conference", "A Letter from a Daughter", "Three Pretenders" and "A Celebration Meeting" in the form of "A Mountain Shrine".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The creation of "A Mountain Shrine"-type drama was the great event opening the new era of Juche-oriented revolutionary drama and constituted a landmark for the construction of Juche-oriented drama art and the development of the world drama. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the Workers' Party of Korea's policy and theory on drama art advanced in the creation of the "A Mountain Shrine"-style dramas, masterpieces including the revolutionary dramas "Under the Banner of Victory," "Wish" and "Mother's Request" were created one by one.

Rodong Sinmun Flails U.S. Dangerous Plan for Preemptive Strike
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- The U.S. Department of Defense worked out a plan to increase the bomb loading capability of the B-2 strategic bomber and this is intended to perfect the U.S. capabilities for preemptive strike, says Rodong Sinmun in a news analysis Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the DPRK is made the target of the preemptive strike, the analyst goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are going to load B-2 with a super large bomb capable of destroying underground structures which can be controlled by a satellite. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is the main target among those objects which they seek to strike by loading the bomber with the extra large bomb 6.25 meters long which they have developed and put on the production line. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "OPLAN 5027" and other military strike scenarios worked out by the U.S. to make a preemptive attack at the DPRK include plans to strike and destroy first major military setups of the DPRK. When developing the extra large bomb capable of penetrating deep underground, the U.S. did not conceal that it was designed to strike the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Judging from all this, we may say that the U.S. is hastening preparations to mount a preemptive attack on the DPRK at the last stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Various types of U.S. battleships are frequenting Japanese ports near the Korean Peninsula. This suggests that the sinister U.S. scheme to make a preemptive strike at the DPRK is entering the practical stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. eagerly waits for an opportunity to launch a preemptive strike while pretending to seek reconciliation with the DPRK, the hostile relations between the DPRK and the U.S. will never be settled and the situation will get more complicated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The option of preemptive strike is not a monopoly of the U.S.

Rodong Sinmun on Absolute Standard for Settling National Issue 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- Independent will and interests of all members of the nation alone can serve as an absolute standard for solving the issue related to its destiny. Rodong Sinmun Wednesday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans who live separated in the two parts are committed to achieving national reunification, their common will and interests, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National reunification is, in essence, the cause of achieving national independence as it is aimed at putting an end to foreign domination and interference and attaining national independence. It is the task to be fulfilled for the sake of the Korean nation. The Koreans in the north and the south and overseas have a vital interests in it, in reality. More than six decades have passed since Korea was divided into two by outside forces. National reunification has, therefore, become the cherished desire of the Koreans. It represents the will of the nation and its implementation would meet its vital interests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When handling any national issue, the issue of inter-Korean relations, Koreans should regard the unity and reunification of the nation, its will and interests, as a standard for settling it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They can never achieve independence by depending upon outside forces in settling the national issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 era of reunification proved in practice that neither relations with any foreign forces nor ism should be placed above the interests of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans who stake their destiny on national reunification should solve all issues on the principle of defending the nation and giving priority to it, regarding its will and interests as an absolute standard in order to achieve independence. There can be no other way for them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans are the driving force for national reunification and no one can replace them in this matter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are called upon to regard the common will and interests of the nation as the best standard under any circumstances and carve out their destiny independently by resolutely rejecting the foreign interference and pressure according to their own view and judgement in the spirit of "By our nation itself".

Dissolution of S. Korea-U.S. "Combined Forces Command" Urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- The United States invented the south Korea-U.S. "Combined Forces Command", a military tool for aggression, on Nov. 7, Juche 67 (1978), in a bid to perpetuate its military occupation of south Korea and realize its wild ambition for aggression on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Newspapers here today carry signed articles in this regard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun says in an article that in south Korea the "command" has so far worked out war scenarios for aggression on the DPRK and supervised all the military exercises and arms buildup to carry them into practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also backed the pro-American fascist dictatorial regimes by force of arms while commanding behind the scene the military suppression of the south Korean people's massive struggle for democracy against dictatorship, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That is why the people from all walks of life in south Korea have strongly demanded the dissolution of the criminal "command" from long ago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seized with uneasiness at the increasing desire of the south Korean people for independence against the U.S. and for peace against war, the U.S. is resorting to more cunning tricks to keep its military occupation and domination over south Korea. It seeks to nominally disorganize the "command" through the transfer of the "right to command wartime operations" and, instead, use other military mechanism more powerful than it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. still remains unchanged in its intention to perpetuate its military presence in south Korea and realize its design for domination over the whole of Korea. This is proved by the fact that the U.S. is working hard to maintain and reinforce the "UN Command" in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After all, there will be no change even if the "Combined Forces Command" is dissolved through the transfer of the "right to command wartime operations." The "Combined Forces Command" and the "UN Command" are different in name, but much the same in intrinsic nature as they serve as a criminal military tool for occupation, domination, aggression and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that either dissolution of the "command" or transfer of the "right" will be nothing but a gimcrack as long as the U.S. forces remain in south Korea. The U.S. should take immediate measures to pull back its forces, not resorting to palpable deceptive tricks, it stresses.

Struggle against Presidential Candidate from GNP Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- Members of the Solidarity for Progress of south Korea reportedly called upon the people to turn out in the struggle against Ri Myong Bak, a presidential candidate from the Grand National Party, as part of the actions against conservatism in Seoul on Nov. 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They accused Ri Myong Bak of deceiving the people with lies though he has committed many scandals including "false moving-in" and "BBK stock price manipulation", adding that he is not qualified for "presidential candidacy" as he is keen on double-dealing tactics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They denounced Ri for raising both hands in support of the extension of the presence of troops in Iraq and openly letting loose such reckless remarks as describing the "presidential elections" as "confrontation between pro-north left wing and conservative right wing".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon the people to turn out in the campaign to denounce Ri Myong Bak hell-bent on telling lies and perpetrating anti-reunification acts.

Vigorous Anti-U.S. Struggle Urged in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification (Pomminryon) reportedly issued a statement on November 4 on the lapse of 78 years since the Kwangju student incident. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The incident on November 3, 1929, shook the Japanese imperialist colonial ruling system to its very foundation, the statement said, adding: Today the youth and students should shatter the outsiders' persistent domination over south Korea and interference in its affairs by inheriting the fighting spirit displayed by the righteous students in Kwangju 78 years ago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an urgent task for the youth and students to take the lead in the sacred struggle to remove the pro-U.S. flunkeyist forces and drive out the U.S. forces from this land under the uplifted banner of "By our nation itself" in the June 15 era, the statement stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It declared that the South Headquarters of Pomminryon would certainly put an end to pro-American sycophantic policy in south Korea and expel the U.S. forces from there, together with all the youth and students advocating justice.

S. Korea-U.S. "Annual Security Consultative Meeting" Flailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 7 (KCNA) -- A rally for denouncing the 39th south Korea-U.S. "annual security consultative meeting" was reportedly held in Seoul on Nov. 3 under the sponsorship of the Solidarity for Progress of south Korea, the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions, the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification and other civic and public organizations of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the rally speakers noted that the meeting is expected to discuss the issues of expanding the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek, "transferring the right to control wartime operations" and coordinating the role of the "UN Command" and decide on such matters as scenarios of war against the DPRK, command of operations, maneuvers of forces and forced purchase of arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is said that even after "transfer of the right to control wartime operations" the south Korean air force will be put under the control of the U.S. air force commander, they pointed out, adding this means that in actuality the U.S. forces would maintain their right to control all operations of the south Korean forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The belligerent forces at home and abroad are scheming to make the south Korea-U.S. "Combined Forces Command" function as the "UN Command", they said, charging that the U.S. and the Defence Ministry of south Korea are committing crimes, going against the development of history.

Se acredita ante Kim Yong Nam el embajador de Myanmar 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 7 de noviembre (ATCC) -- U Thein Lwin presento el dia 7 en el Palacio de los Congresos Mansudae ante el presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, Kim Yong Nam, sus cartas credenciales que le acreditan como embajador extraordinario y plenipotenciario de la Union de Myanmar en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Luego de recibirlas, Kim departio con el diplomatico.

Kim Yong Nam envia telegrama de consuelo al presidente mexicano
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 7 de noviembre (ATCC) -- El presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, Kim Yong Nam, envio el dia 6 un telegrama de consuelo a Felipe Calderon Hinojosa, presidente de los Estados Unidos Mexicanos en relacion con que este pais sufrio muchas perdidas humanas y materiales debido a la lluvia torrencial sin precedente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El remitente desea que el presidente y el gobierno de Mexico liquiden cuanto antes las consecuencias de desastre natural y estabilicen la vida de los damnificados por la inundacion.

ATCC comenta viles actos de los "politicos" estupidos de EE.UU.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 7 de noviembre (ATCC) -- En estos dias, las fuerzas conservadoras intransigentes de Estados Unidos vuelven a recurrir a la censura y calumnia contra la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El neoconservador Bolton habla de que "es absurdo confiar que el Norte de Corea cumpla su promesa", "la historia muestra que el Norte de Corea no abandona jamas por si mismo las armas nucleares" y "solo el tiempo testimoniara que EE.UU. fuera enganado".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Para colmo, dio a luz hasta el libro "La capitulacion no es la opcion" escrito por si mismo. En el senalo que algunas personalidades de la Administracion norteamericana hacen "diplomacia absurda" con la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tales palabras no valen nada siendo refunfunos del hombre expulsado del gobierno. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    Tambien no pasa de ser un aullido desesperado para danar a toda costa la imagen de la RPDC que aprecia la promesa y la confianza. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El problema reside en que Bolton y otras fuerzas conservadoras intransigentes yanquis maniobran obstinadamente para frustrar el acuerdo de las conversaciones a 6 partes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Bolton "llama" a los parlamentarios a oponerse al citado acuerdo; unos congresistas republicanos expresaron la posicion de "no aprobar los gastos concernientes al ofrecimiento del aceite pesado de la administracion a la RPDC" y las fuerzas conservadoras de la administracion dijeron que "si el Norte de Corea no cumple su promesa, debe aplicar el latigo".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Como es notorio por todos, los acuerdos aprobados en la cita a 6 bandas aclaran los deberes de los paises participantes en esta a ser cumplidos por la desnuclearizacion de la Peninsula Coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ahora, la RPDC y EE.UU. efectuan con sinceridad las conversaciones de expertos y otros dialogos en varias esferas. Tambien, se impulsa en etapa practica el ofrecimiento del aceite pesado de EE.UU. a Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A pesar de esto, las fuerzas conservadoras intransigentes de EE.UU. tratan de convertir en un papel mojado el mismo acuerdo de las conversaciones a 6 bandas y detener la accion de la administracion norteamericana para el cumplimiento del acuerdo, lo cual demuestra fehacientemente que ellas no desean la desnuclearizacion de la Peninsula Coreana  sino persiguen solo el enfrentamiento. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tales maniobras causaran solo la censura de la sociedad internacional siendo actos viejos y viles de quienes no agradan la corriente de la epoca hacia el alivio de tension en torno al problema nuclear de la Peninsula Coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  No es casual que la AP comento que "Bolton se esfuerza por llevar al fracaso el acuerdo de las conversaciones a 6 bandas".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Las fuerzas conservadoras intransigentes de EE.UU. deben actuar con prudencia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Son invariables la posicion de la RPDC de realizar la desnuclearizacion de la Peninsula Coreana y sus sinceros  esfuerzos por llevarla a cabo.

Inaugurada exposicion artistica por el Dia Cultural de Cuba
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 7 de noviembre (ATCC) -- La Exposicion Artistica por el Dia Cultural de Cuba quedo inaugurada el dia 7 en la Casa Internacional de Cultura de Pyongyang por los auspicios de la Embajada de la Republica de Cuba acreditada en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion fueron invitados el vicepresidente del Comite Coreano de Relaciones Culturales con el Extranjero, Jon Yong Jin, y otros funcionarios, trabajadores capitalinos, los representantes diplomaticos y otros miembros de las embajadas de varios paises en Coroea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tambien, estuvieron presentes el embajador Jose Manuel Galego Montano y otros miembros de la sede diplomatica cubana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el acto inaugural hubo discursos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los participantes recorrieron las obras de bellas artes, bordados y productos de artes menores que muestran el talento e inteligencia del pueblo cubano y aspectos de desarrollo de la cultura nacional cubana.
